I"A<p>Social exclusion and rejection can cause experiences of physical numbness and a lack of emotion.  Baumeister et al, 2003</p>

<p>Researchers who studied people who had been excluded from a society or group found that it was common for them to shut down their emotional response rather than experiencing heightened states of distress.</p>

<p>“It was as though they had been hit with a stun gun”</p>

<p>They suggest could be an adaptive response to prevent retaliation against the group and to keep painful emotions out of awareness.</p>

<p>(K. D. Williams, 2001).</p>
